    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-06-03</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-07-07T21:45:22Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>National Hate Crimes Hotline Act of 2009 - Authorizes the Attorney General to award grants to: (1) private, nonprofit entities to establish and operate a national, toll-free telephone hotline and an Internet website to assist victims of hate crimes; and (2) state and local law enforcement entities for educational and training programs on solving hate crimes and establishing dialogues with members of communities who are at-risk of being victims of hate crimes.</p> <p>Directs the Attorney General to establish a program for awarding grants to local organizations to establish or expand programs that provide services to victims of hate crimes. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>National Hate Crimes Hotline Act of 2009</title>
    <titles>
      <item>
